begin
reserve X for BCK-algebra;
reserve IT for non empty (Subset of X);
theorem
Th26: (for X being BCK-algebra holds (IT is (Commutative-Ideal of X) implies IT is (Ideal of X)))
proof
let X being BCK-algebra;
assume A1: IT is (Commutative-Ideal of X);
A2: (for x,y being (Element of X) holds ((( x \ y ) in IT & y in IT) implies x in IT))
proof
let x being (Element of X),y being (Element of X);
assume that
A3: ( x \ y ) in IT
and
A4: y in IT;
A5: ( x \ ( ( 0. X ) \ ( ( 0. X ) \ x ) ) ) = ( x \ ( ( 0. X ) \ ( x ` ) ) )
.= ( x \ ( ( 0. X ) \ ( 0. X ) ) ) by BCIALG_1:def 8
.= ( x \ ( 0. X ) ) by BCIALG_1:def 5
.= x by BCIALG_1:2;
( ( x \ ( 0. X ) ) \ y ) in IT by A3,BCIALG_1:2;
hence thesis by A1,A4,A5,CKB41:def 1;
end;
( 0. X ) in IT by A1,CKB41:def 1;
hence thesis by A1,A2,BCIALG_1:def 18;
end;
